name: raw_msg_id
description: Unique identifier for this message generated during ingestion

name: raw_vessel_id
description: Unique identifier for the vessel generated during ingestion

name: timestamp
description: This is the unix timestamp for the time the message was received by the original receiver.  You should use this as the effective timestamp for the message

name: ingested_at
description: The exact moment this record was ingested by us (GFW) this is when the raw record is stored in our raw BQ tables

name: timestamp_date
description: This is the day when the message was received by the original receiver in UTC
